# Rendered diagram artifacts — regenerate with diagram/render_diagram.py.
*.png
*.svg

# ...except the tree renders themselves, which ARE committed and linked from the
# README via their raw.githubusercontent URLs, so the images never depend on
# GitHub Pages being enabled. This is the root page plus one per collapsed
# subtree (train_tree__<id>.{png,svg}). Regenerate with diagram/render_diagram.py.
!diagram/train_tree.png
!diagram/train_tree.svg
!diagram/train_tree__*.png
!diagram/train_tree__*.svg

# The generated .drawio IS committed: the repo is public, so draw.io serves it
# read-only from its raw GitHub URL (see the view link build_diagram.py prints).
# Regenerate with diagram/build_diagram.py.

# CI render / Pages output (generated by .github/workflows/diagram.yml — never committed)
diagram/export/
_site/

